Location: Zeeland, South Holland and North Brabant .largest floodings on Schouwen-Duiveland, Tholen, Sint Philipsland, Goeree-Overflakkee, the Hoeksche Waard, Voorne-Putten and Alblasserwaard. Parts of Zuid-Beveland, Noord-Beveland, IJselmonde, Pernis, Rozenburg, Walcheren and Land van Altena, Willemstad, Nieuw-Vossemeer, Zeeuws-Vlaanderenwere flooded.

Origin: Torrential rainfall caused by a slow-moving area of low pressure – named “Bernd”
